    "plan_content": "## Plan Summary\n\nAfter thoroughly exploring `src/pipelines.js` and `src/models.js`, here's the complete implementation plan for the `image-text-to-text` pipeline:\n\n**Only one file needs to change: `src/pipelines.js`**\n\n### 4 surgical edits:\n\n**① Import (line 43)** — Add `AutoModelForImageTextToText` to the `./models.js` import block between `AutoModelForImageFeatureExtraction` and `PreTrainedModel`.\n\n**② New class (after line 2779)** — Inserted right after `DocumentQuestionAnsweringPipeline`'s closing brace. The pattern combines both reference pipelines:\n- Like `DocumentQuestionAnsweringPipeline`: takes `(image, text, generate_kwargs)`, processes one image at a time, tokenizes text to get `input_ids`\n- Like `ImageToTextPipeline`: calls `model.generate()` and decodes with `batch_decode(..., { skip_special_tokens: true })`, returns `[{ generated_text }]`\n- Uses the already-existing `TextImagePipelineConstructorArgs` typedef (model + tokenizer + processor)\n\n**③ SUPPORTED_TASKS entry (after line 3341)** — After `\"document-question-answering\"`, registers the pipeline with `AutoModelForImageTextToText`, `AutoTokenizer`, `AutoProcessor`, default model `onnx-community/Florence-2-base-ft`, and `type: \"multimodal\"`.\n\n**④ Factory JSDoc (after line 3427)** — One new bullet point in alphabetical order in the `pipeline()` task list.\n\nNo other files require changes — `src/transformers.js` already re-exports everything via `export * from './pipelines.js'`.",
